   <h1>The Troll&#39;s Bane Chronicle</h1>

   <h2>The fifth year of the new era: January</h2>

<p>In the year 5 of the new era on January the 2nd, Farok demands in public for his items to be returned, which he had lost in a confrontation with Persephonie. </p>
<p>In the year 5 of the new era on January the 4th, Alora Ironforge warns the dwarves of Silverbrand of a threat imposed by a demon. </p>
<p>In the year 5 of the new era on January the 8th, Ules Felko tries to establish a militia to protect Troll's Bane. The public however speaks against the suggestion, with a hint directed towards the Town Guard and the Grey Rose. </p>
<p>In the year 5 of the new era on January the 10th, Mary asks the Triumvirate for a playground for the town's children. </p>
<p>In the year 5 of the new era on January the 11th, the Clan of the Axe determines that all information involving the demon that had fallen into Silverbrand must be made public. </p>
<p>In the year 5 of the new era on January the 12th, Damien announces that Sideon Vilarion is initiated as a Novice of the Order of Grey Light. </p>
<p>In the year 5 of the new era on January the 13th, Jeremy Willowbrook announces the opening of the Varshikar Bakery. </p>
<p>In the year 5 of the new era on January the 14th, the Clan of the Axe announces that Belegi Zahar is elected new leader of the clan. </p>
<p>In the year 5 of the new era on January the 14th, Kerigan van Ildoran bids his friends farewell. </p>
<p>In the year 5 of the new era on January the 14th, the Clan of the Axe demands that the conflict between Troll's Bane and the Bloodskulls is ceased, and furthermore declares that they shall remain neutral. </p>
<p>In the year 5 of the new era on January the 15th, Gwynnether von Glanwen declares in the name of the Town Guard that the orcs of the Bloodskulls are outlawed, and calls the citizens of the town to defend themselves and the city. </p>
<p>In the year 5 of the new era on January the 17th, Lorck demands that the attacks against Varshikar are ended. It remains unknown who the attackers were. </p>
<p>In the year 5 of the new era on January the 17th, the Bloodskulls publish their claim for the lands west of Varshikar. </p>
<p>In the year 5 of the new era on January the 19th, a piece of poetry titled "Ten - A Prophetic Poem" appears on the shop's wall. </p>
<p>In the year 5 of the new era on January the 19th, John Irenicus warns of drinking any water from the fountain, because a man named Keldor has poisoned them. </p>
<p>In the year 5 of the new era on January the 21st, Athian demands the immediate release of his sister Mary, who was brought by John Irenicus into the Grey Retreat. John thereupon declares, that the girl is a child of Bjolmur, but his words seem to fall onto deaf ears. </p>
<p>In the year 5 of the new era on January the 22nd, Lorck threatens to kill all members of the Grey Rose and the Town Guard, in case Kaja is not released. </p>
<p>In the year 5 of the new era on January the 22nd, the Brotherhood of Knowledge is dissolved again, after several members depart from the society due to inactivity and doubtful procedures of action of their leader. </p>
<p>In the year 5 of the new era on January the 23rd, the Clan of the Axe publishes a declaration which states that any member of dwarvenkind may join the clan, even if they are incapable of comprehending the old tongue. </p>
<p>In the year 5 of the new era on January the 24th, Lennier expresses his thanks to the citizens and friends of Troll's Bane, who fought side by side against the orcish attack. </p>
<p>In the year 5 of the new era on January the 24th, the Elders of the elvenkind declare war upon the Bloodskulls, if they should fail to release their captive Gwynnether and deliver Misjbar to them. </p>
<p>In the year 5 of the new era on January the 25th, and after her release, Gwynnether von Glanwen appeals to Troll's Bane and the Bloodskulls to lance a new beginning. </p>
<p>In the year 5 of the new era on January the 26th, the Triumvirate suggests a truce between them and the Bloodskulls, but this suggestion remains completely unanswered. </p>
<p>In the year 5 of the new era on January the 28th, Gwynnether von Glanwen and John Irenicus are wed by King Tialdin. </p>
<p>In the year 5 of the new era on January the 30th, Hermie reminds everyone that strangers have no permission to cut wood in Greenbriar.</p>

